OL,3,CWhat are cloudbursts? The deadly
OL,4,Cweather event in India and Pakistan
OL,6,F"Rising global temperatures have
OL,7,Fsupercharged the hydrologic cycle,
OL,8,Fleading to more intense and erratic
OL,9,Frainfall," said Khalid Khan, a former
OL,10,Fspecial secretary for climate change
OL,11,Fin Pakistan and chairman of climate
OL,12,Finitiative Planet Pulse.
OL,14,F"In our northern regions, warming
OL,15,Faccelerates glacier melt, adds
OL,16,Fexcessive moisture to the atmosphere,
OL,17,Fand destabilises mountain slopes."
OL,19,F"In short, climate change is making
OL,20,Frare events more frequent, and
OL,21,Ffrequent events more destructive."
